-- IBM and Sun broke off acquisition talks: report
-- 
-- Sun Apr 5, 2009 5:38pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/04/05/us-ibm-sun-idUSTRE5342U020090405

 

 (Reuters) - International Business Machines Corp and Sun Microsystems Inc broke off talks aimed at a $7 billion acquisition, the Wall Street Journal reported on Sunday. 

 Talks between IBM and Sun were on the brink of collapse, threatening to undermine a potential $7 billion acquisition, according to the newspaper.